text:
<@U057J8HJZMF> Good news, I think I figured out the issue! There's logic in the frontend that assumes you have data populated in your database for "watchlist" -- if you don't, it gives that "watchlist.map() is not a function" error. We'll work on fixing that in the future, but for now if you add at least one watchlist to your database manually, it should work. Note, it will make you add data for other tables first because of foreign key constraints -- here's what I used and it worked for me:

```insert into user (id, pw_hash, username)
values (1,"password","username");

insert into user_details (id, user_id)
values (1,1);

insert into watchlist (id, list_type, name, user_details_id)
values(1,"custom","firstWatchlist",1);```

text:
Made some progress!

My latest branch, *<https://github.com/corypride/teamStruggle/tree/rework-fronend-auth-backend-without-userdetails|rework-fronend-auth-backend-without-userdetails>*, has register and login connected and working correctly, as well as the profile page! I added a HTTPservletresponse parameter in the authentication controller that sets a cookie on register and login. That cookie is what allows the frontend to send future api requests correctly. I also added this line -- "axios.defaults.withCredentials = true;" to the top of Profile.js and Search.js, which ensures the axios requests sends the cookie with every request, which allows it to access those endpoints.

However, adding to watchlists from search still isn't working because for some reason the post mapping doesn't automatically include the cookie when it sends requests. That's the next step!
